          {
            "text": "In this final study, we'll see a windmill as it occurred in Carlos Torre Repetto vs Emanuel Lasker (1925). \n\nA windmill is a tactic that consists of a series of repetitive checks and captures with discovered check.\n\nIt's a really strong tactic because you can take a lot of material with check and your opponent cannot do anything.",
